# Python 
## Logging
- Always use loguru for logging. Check the latest version on the internet before installing.

## Package and Environment Management
- Always use `uv`. Check the latest version on the internet before installing.

## Code style
- Double quotes

## Testing instructions
- Add or update tests for the code you change, even if nobody asked.

## Version Control
- Commits must follow the simplest conventional git commit formats, like "feat: bla bla"
- Commits cannot be specific - they have to convey the MEANING of the changes.
- Commits must be very very short. 
- Each commit cannot be muliline. 
- Separate into multiple `-m` commit messages if you have to.